entry.tran: 出席人数;到场人数;参加人数
entry.def: The turnout at an event is the number of people who go to it or take part in it.

example.ex: On the big night there was a massive turnout...
example.tran: 在这个重要的夜晚，有大批人出席。

example.ex: It was a marvellous afternoon with a huge turnout of people.
example.tran: 那是个美妙的下午，出席人数众多。

entry.def: The turnout in an election is the number of people who vote in it, as a proportion of the number of people who have the right to vote in it.

example.ex: Election officials said the turnout of voters was low...
example.tran: 选举官员称选民的投票率很低。

means.word_mean: 1. the group that gathers together for a particular occasion;
2. a part of a road that has been widened to allow cars to pass or park
3. a short stretch of railroad track used to store rolling stock or enable trains on the same line to pass
4. what is produced in a given time period
6. attendance for a particular event or purpose (as to vote in an election);
7. (ballet) the outward rotation of a dancer's leg from the hip
